This paper investigates the emergence of structural bias in Differential Evolution (DE) algorithm, which is commonly used in optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the constraint handling technique, which is related to optimization problems and can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study also involves statistical analysis, which can be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the potential weaknesses of the algorithm, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves testing and analyzing different configurations of DE, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
